

Current version:
- now the Simple Submission Form support multiple input files (LC)
- the help section of the submission form new displayes properly also html symbol like <> (LC)
- build.properties and etc/opal.properties have been renamed with .template extension (LC)
- the output page after the submission is now open in a new browser (LC)
- the NBCR logo is now transparent (LC)
- the "Number of jobs currently running" chart is rendered with different colors (LC) 
- Made the code compatible with java 1.4 (LC)
- updated the way opal handles symlinked working directories - now we do
  not need Tomcat to be on NFS (SK)
- now the charts use a thicker brush in the statistics page (LC)
- patched some Boolean comparison in the jsp which caused errors with older jsp compiler (SK)
- nicer error page when a Data Based connection is not present (LC)
- the output files can now be retrieved as zip file if a parameter
  (data.archive) is set in the opal.properties (SK)
- the summary page now displays the data lifetime that can be set in the opal.properties (LC)
- add a chart with the running jobs in the statistics page (LC)
- correct the load-on-startup order of the various servlets which in some case could cause a missing DB connection (LC)
- remove an error in the statistics page the URL used for the immages to display the charts was wrong (LC)

1.9 alpha:
- Opal Dashboard: it is a web based interface that provide an easy way to check the 
  status of the opal installation. 
- If an external database has been used the Dashboard can also display chart with 
  access and usage statistics
- Dynamic Interface Generation for Opal: This web based interface allows user to 
  invoke Opal based service directly from their browser. It is also possible to 
  create customized submission form based on the command line syntax
- Modified and streamlined the install and upgrade process - now bundling
  axis webapp with Opal, thus reducing an external prerequisite
